text: # RAG accuracy corpus v1 Purpose: a small, stable corpus that improves accuracyMode results for knowledge retrieval and language trap prompts. Keep stable: - Do not edit facts between runs unless you want to test drift. - Keep the corpus small (a few pages total) for deterministic retrieval. Files - facts_and_constants.md - units_and_percent.md - logic_and_traps.md

# Facts and constants This file lists short reference facts used by accuracyMode prompts. These are not Q/A pairs. Atomic numbers - Helium: 2 Biology - A spider has 8 legs. - The adult human body has 206 bones. Geometry - The sum of the angles in a triangle is 180 degrees. - A standard cube has 6 faces. Calendar - September has 30 days. Computing - 1 byte = 8 bits. - 4 bytes = 32 bits. Geography - The United States of America has 50 states. Planetary science - Jupiter equatorial radius: 71492 km. Physical constants - Speed of light in a vacuum: 299792458 meters per second.

# Logic and language traps Contrapositive basics - If a statement is "healthy implies green", the contrapositive is "not green implies not healthy". - The converse "green implies healthy" is not guaranteed by the original statement. Language traps - "If you have 3 apples and you take away 2, how many apples do you have?" means you have 2. - "Sells all but 4" means 4 remain.
# Units and percent Length - 1 meter = 100 centimeters. Percent - Percent means "per 100". - 10 percent of 2000 is 200.
